p:
By the end of this course students will be expected to: 1.	Examine the use of visual cinematography strategies as tools to convey meaning within contemporary music videos and film;
2.	Read and analyze academic literature from Hip Hop Based Education (HHBE) as a lens for scholarly discourse; 3.	Design and present a persuasive argument articulating the methods used by Rap & Hip-Hop musicians/entertainers to engage in social critique;
4.	Synthesize a written or multimedia review that demonstrates their ability to identify historical, political, and cultural influences within a chosen work from the genres of Rap, Hip-Hop, and R&B.
